ets submerged in a wave at the beach, don\u0026#39;t sweat it — the Monster S150 can easily handle it. What\u0026#39;s great is that if you need a little more power, you can always pair two of these speakers together for a more impressive sound. \u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eAnd when it comes to connectivity, you\u0026#39;re going to get a ton of options, from Bluetooth, AUX, USB, and even a microSD card slot. There\u0026#39;s even an RGB light on the top of the speaker to really create a mood when you\u0026#39;re listening to your music. Again, you\u0026#39;re getting all of this for just $30, which is an absolute steal. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                    \n                            \n\n\n\n\n        \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n            \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
